body:
It&#039;s pretty disgusting seeing Twitch and Vayne scaling off just existing for half the average game time and becoming insane powerhouses

Then there is Sona who lives life in the slow lane and the only thought process behind picking her is &quot;I sure hope this game lasts 40 minutes so I can get to do something&quot;
Hoping that the incoming slight mana revert puts Sona back into the realm of existence earlygame, but looking at other factors in the game I can&#039;t help but think that a &quot;Scaling support that needs more gold then a ADC&quot; is still the least desirable thing to have backing up a ADC
